{%- comment -%}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BUY BUTTONS
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This component is used to show the buy buttons

********************************************
Supported variables
********************************************

* product: the product from which to show the buttons
* show_payment_button: if we show or not the dynamic checkout button
* show_gift_card_recipient: for gift card products, an optional message/email to be sent to the recipient
* button_size: the size of the button (default to xl if none is passed)
* pre_order: custom vcollect, forces the pre-order label even when the product does not use the pre-order template.
  Accepts either the boolean true or the string "true" returned by 'pre-order-check'
* atc_button_background: the background of the ATC button
* atc_button_text_color: the text color of the ATC button
* payment_button_background: the custom dynamic checkout button background
* payment_button_text_color: the custom dynamic checkout button text color
* form_id: if specified, define the form ID linked to this input
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign variant_picker_block = section.blocks | where: 'type', 'variant_picker' | first -%}

{%- comment -%}
Custom vcollect: Impact decides "pre-order" from the template suffix alone, which forces someone to move a product to
another template on its release day and back again. Here pre-order is derived from the release date (see
'pre-order-check'), so the caller passes it in.

The flag is folded into the template attribute rather than only into the Liquid label, because the buy-buttons web
component re-renders the label on every variant change and reads that attribute to choose between "Pré-commander" and
"Ajouter au panier". Setting only the Liquid label would make the button revert to "Ajouter au panier" as soon as the
shopper picks another variant. The component tests it with .includes('pre-order'), so appending is enough.

pre_order is matched against true AND against the string 'true' on purpose. Callers get the state from
'pre-order-check', which is a snippet and therefore returns a captured string, and in Liquid an EMPTY string is truthy:
a bare `if pre_order` would turn every product into a pre-order at any call site that forwards the capture directly.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign is_pre_order = false
  if pre_order == true or pre_order == 'true'
    assign is_pre_order = true
  endif

  assign buy_buttons_template = product.template_suffix

  if is_pre_order
    unless buy_buttons_template contains 'pre-order'
      assign buy_buttons_template = buy_buttons_template | append: ' pre-order'
    endunless
  endif

  comment
    A product put on Impact's native pre-order template counts as a pre-order too, otherwise it would get the
    "Pré-commander" label but keep the express checkout button and reach the cart with no mention of a later shipment,
    which is precisely the gap this snippet exists to close. One state, whichever way it was declared.
  endcomment
  if buy_buttons_template contains 'pre-order'
    assign is_pre_order = true
  endif

  assign release_date_formatted = product.metafields.vcollect.date_sortie.value | date: '%d/%m/%Y'
-%}

{%- comment -%}
Custom vcollect: the dynamic checkout button ("Acheter maintenant") is dropped on a pre-order. It sends the shopper
straight to payment, skipping the cart, which is the one place where the shipping date is repeated before paying. On a
product that ships weeks later, taking the money without that step invites chargebacks.

Forced here rather than at each call site so the product page and the quick buy drawer cannot disagree.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if is_pre_order -%}
  {%- assign show_payment_button = false -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- form 'product', product, is: 'product-form', id: form_id -%}
  <input type="hidden" {% if variant_picker_block != blank %}disabled{% endif %} name="id" value="{{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.id }}">

  {%- comment -%}
  Custom vcollect: a line item property carries the pre-order status into the cart, the checkout, the confirmation
  email and the admin order. Nothing else does: the "Pré-commander" label lives on the product page only, so without
  this the shopper pays on a checkout that looks like any other and expects a normal delivery.

  A line item property is the native way to do this, no app involved. The name has no leading underscore on purpose,
  that prefix is what hides a property from the shopper (see 'line-item'), and here it must stay visible.

  The date is written into the value at add-to-cart time rather than read back later, so the order keeps the date that
  was promised even if the release is pushed back afterwards.

  Guarded on the date being present as well: a product sold as a pre-order through the native template may carry no
  release date, and a property reading "Expédition à partir du" with nothing after it is worse than no property.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if is_pre_order and release_date_formatted != blank -%}
    {%- assign pre_order_property_name = 'product.general.pre_order_property_name' | t -%}
    {%- assign pre_order_property_value = 'product.general.pre_order_property_value' | t: date: release_date_formatted -%}
    <input type="hidden" name="properties[{{ pre_order_property_name | escape }}]" value="{{ pre_order_property_value | escape }}">
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- assign button_disabled = false -%}
  {%- assign button_size = button_size | default: 'xl' -%}

  {%- if product.selected_or_first_available_variant.available -%}
    {%- if is_pre_order -%}
      {%- capture button_content -%}{{ 'product.general.pre_order_button' | t }}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- else -%}
      {%- capture button_content -%}{{ 'product.general.add_to_cart_button' | t }}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- capture button_content -%}{{ 'product.general.sold_out_button' | t }}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- assign button_disabled = true -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  <div class="v-stack gap-4">
    {%- if product.gift_card? and show_gift_card_recipient -%}
      <gift-card-recipient class="gift-card-recipient v-stack gap-3">
        {%- assign checkbox_label = 'gift_card.recipient.checkbox' | t -%}
        {%- render 'checkbox', label: checkbox_label, name: 'properties[__shopify_send_gift_card_to_recipient]' -%}

        <div class="gift-card-recipient__fields js:hidden">
          <div class="fieldset">
            {%- liquid
              assign recipient_email_label = 'gift_card.recipient.email_label' | t
              render 'input', type: 'email', label: recipient_email_label, name: 'properties[Recipient email]', value: form.email, required: true

              assign recipient_name_label = 'gift_card.recipient.name_label' | t
              render 'input', label: recipient_name_label, name: 'properties[Recipient name]', value: form.name

              assign message_label = 'gift_card.recipient.message_label' | t
              render 'input', label: message_label, name: 'properties[Recipient message]', value: form.message, multiline: 3, maxlength: 200, show_max_characters_count: true
            -%}
          </div>
        </div>
      </gift-card-recipient>
    {%- endif -%}

    <buy-buttons class="buy-buttons {% if show_payment_button %}buy-buttons--multiple{% endif %}" template="{{ buy_buttons_template | escape }}" form="{{ form_id }}">
      {%- render 'button', content: button_content, type: 'submit', size: button_size, disabled: button_disabled, secondary: show_payment_button, subdued: button_disabled, background: atc_button_background, text_color: atc_button_text_color -%}

      {%- if show_payment_button -%}
        {{- form | payment_button -}}

        <style>
          #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} .shopify-payment-button {
          {%- unless product.selected_or_first_available_variant.available -%}
            display: none;
          {%- endunless -%}

          {%- if payment_button_background != blank and payment_button_background != 'rgba(0,0,0,0)' -%}
            --button-background: {{ payment_button_background.rgb }};
          {%- endif -%}

          {%- if payment_button_text_color != blank and payment_button_text_color != 'rgba(0,0,0,0)' -%}
            --button-text-color: {{ payment_button_text_color.rgb }};
          {%- endif -%}
          }
        </style>
      {%- endif -%}
    </buy-buttons>
  </div>
{%- endform -%}